\f2\b\fs28 \cf0 \strokec2 4. Waqf (Perpetual Endowment) Asset Management\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Waqf is Islamic endowment \'97 assets dedicated permanently to charitable purposes. The global waqf corpus is estimated at $1 trillion but massively underleveraged because waqf managers cannot invest in interest-bearing instruments and have no rigorous alternative.\
The Ackerer framework gives waqf fund managers a complete asset management toolkit:\
The endowment earns continuous premium \uc0\u954  \'d7 (corpus_value - fair_value) without interest. The corpus is invested in perpetual sukuk (Layer 2) and takaful pools (Layer 3), both priced by the same mathematics. Distribution events \'97 when the endowment pays out to beneficiaries \'97 are modeled as stopping times \u952  with charity-specific hazard rates.\
The fair value of the entire waqf portfolio at any time is computable in closed form from Proposition 3. Fund managers have a rigorous, sharia-native performance benchmark: is the actual corpus value tracking E[x_\uc0\u952 ]? If not, why?\
This is the first complete asset management framework for waqf that doesn't require borrowing any conventional finance methodology.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
