\f2\b\fs28 \cf0 \strokec2 8. Islamic Pension / Retirement Systems\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Conventional pension funds discount future liabilities at a risk-free interest rate to compute present value. Islamic pension funds cannot do this \'97 there is no interest-free discounting framework in current Islamic finance practice. As a result, Muslim workers in Muslim-majority countries are systematically under-served by retirement finance.\
The Ackerer random time representation provides the solution directly. A pension liability is:\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3\fs26 \cf0 PV(pension) = E[ benefit(x_\uc0\u952 ) ]\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs24 \cf0 where \uc0\u952  is the retirement/death event with hazard rate \u954  (the mortality rate, which can be computed from actuarial tables without any interest component), and x_\u952  is the cost of living at retirement. With \u953 =0, this is fair value without any interest discounting \'97 the "time value" is entirely captured by the probability distribution of \u952 .\
The pension fund earns premium \uc0\u954  \'d7 (fund_value - liability_value) \'d7 dt continuously \'97 the funding payment \'97 which builds the fund to cover liabilities. No interest in the accumulation phase, no interest in the decumulation phase.\
This framework could redesign national pension systems in Indonesia, Malaysia, Turkey, and the GCC \'97 potentially the largest Shariah finance application of all, given aging demographics and the hundreds of millions of Muslim workers currently relying on inadequate, riba-contaminated retirement systems.\
