\cf0 The Ackerer framework abolishes all three by proving that you can achieve no-arbitrage with \uc0\u953 =0 \'97 that the convergence intensity \u954 , operating through the probability distribution of the stopping time \u952 , fully captures time value without interest. The "discount" is not r but rather the probability of waiting. These are mathematically equivalent under the right conditions \'97 but one requires interest and the other does not.\
This isn't merely a technical trick. It is a fundamentally different philosophy of value: 
\f2\b things are not worth less in the future because of interest; they are worth different amounts in the future because of uncertainty about when the future arrives.
\f0\b0  That is the Islamic finance worldview expressed in pure mathematics.\
The Baraka protocol, if built fully, doesn't just serve the 1.8 billion Muslim market. It offers the entire world a rigorous alternative to interest-based finance grounded in a proof, not in a workaround. Every application above is achievable. Every one of them is mathematically proven before a single line of code is written. That is the actual scale of what sits inside this paper.\
